Rates for each reaction channel r_i calculated from current state.\n        2. The timestep tau is chosen randomly from an exponential distribution P ~ e^(-W tau).\n        3.  1863:     """
 1864:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEIR)
 1865:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 1866:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1867:     * Is: symptomatic
 1868:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1869:     * Ic: ICU
 1870:     * Im: Mortality
 1871: 
 1872:     ...
 1873: 
 1874:     Parameters
 1875:     ----------
 1876:      parameters: dict
 1877:         Contains the following keys:
 1878: 
 1879:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 1880:             fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1881:         beta: float
 1882:             rate of spread of infection.
 1883:         gE: float
 1884:             rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1885:         gIa: float
 1886:             rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1887:         gIs: float
 1888:             rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1889:         gIh: float
 1890:             rate of removal for hospitalised individuals.
 1891:         gIc: float
 1892:             rate of removal for idividuals in intensive care.
 1893:         fsa: float
 1894:             fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1895:         fh  : float
 1896:             fraction by which hospitalised individuals are isolated.
 1897:         sa: float, np.array (M,)
 1898:             daily arrival of new susceptables.
 1899:             sa is rate of additional/removal of population by birth etc
 1900:         hh: float, np.array (M,)
 1901:             fraction hospitalised from Is
 1902:         cc: float, np.array (M,)
 1903:             fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 1904:         mm: float, np.array (M,)
 1905:             mortality rate in intensive care
 1906:         seed: long
 1907:             seed for pseudo-random number generator (optional).
 1908:     M: int
 1909:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1910:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1911:     Ni: np.array(8*M, )
 1912:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 1913:     """
 1914:

 2272:     """

 2275: 
 2276:     * Ia: asymptomatic

 2279:     * Ic: ICU
 2280:     * Im: Mortality

 2288: 
 2289:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 2290:             fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 2291:         beta: float
 2292:             rate of spread of infection.
 2293:         gIa: float
 2294:             rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 2295:         gIs: float
 2296:             rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 2297:         fsa: float
 2298:             fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 2299:         gE: float
 2300:             rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 2301:         gA: float
 2302:             rate of removal from activated individuals.
 2303:         gIh: float
 2304:             rate of hospitalisation of infected individuals.
 2305:         gIc: float
 2306:             rate hospitalised individuals are moved to intensive care.
 2307:         seed: long
 2308:             seed for pseudo-random number generator (optional).
 2309:     M: int

 2679:     """
 2680:     Susceptible, Exposed, Asymptomatic and infected, Infected, Removed, Quarantined (SEAIRQ)
 2681: 
 2682:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 2683:     * Is: symptomatic
 2684:     * E: exposed
 2685:     * A: asymptomatic and infectious
 2686:     * Q: quarantined
 2687: 
 2688:     ...
 2689: 
 2690:     Parameters
 2691:     ----------
 2692:     parameters: dict
 2693:         Contains the following keys:
 2694: 
 2695:         alpha: float, np.array(M,)
 2696:             fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 2697:         beta: float
 2698:             rate of spread of infection.
 2699:         gIa: float
 2700:             rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 2701:         gIs: float
 2702:             rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 2703:         gE: float
 2704:             rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 2705:         gA: float
 2706:             rate of removal from activated individuals.
 2707:         fsa: float
 2708:             fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 2709:         tE  : float
 2710:             testing rate and contact tracing of exposeds
 2711:         tA  : float
 2712:             testing rate and contact tracing of activateds
 2713:         tIa: float
 2714:             testing rate and contact tracing of asymptomatics
 2715:         tIs: float
 2716:             testing rate and contact tracing of symptomatics
 2717:         seed: long
 2718:             seed for pseudo-random number generator (optional).
 2719:     M: int
 2720:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 2721:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 2722:     Ni: np.array(6*M, )
 2723:         Initial number in each compartment and class
